description.p:
A fifth aspect of the invention provides a method for assembling at least one piece of at least one chromosome of at least one organism, the method comprising the steps of:
preparing a biological sample comprising the at least one piece of the at least one chromosome;
cross-linking pieces of chromosomes of the prepared biological sample;
fragmenting the cross-linked chromosomes using restriction enzymes of at least two different types;
sequencing the fragments of chromosomes resulting from the fragmenting step; and
assembling the sequenced fragments of chromosomes.

Embodiments of the invention will now be described, by way of example only, and with reference to the following drawings in which:
